[BOTH] ♪ Surf and swim and sand,
it's off to the beach we go! ♪

00:00:35.910 --> 00:00:37.454 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
♪ It's summer, after all ♪

00:00:37.537 --> 00:00:39.456 position:50% align:center
[UTANO]
♪ Summer after all. ♪

00:00:39.539 --> 00:00:43.168 position:50% align:center
[BOTH] ♪ Let's just get crazy
and stupid on the shore ♪

00:00:43.251 --> 00:00:48.757 position:50% align:center
♪ We can start a fire
and have a barbecue ♪

00:00:48.840 --> 00:00:52.802 position:50% align:center
♪ Acting like I'm having fun,
so nobody can ever find out ♪

00:00:52.886 --> 00:00:56.014 position:50% align:center
♪ That I spend most of my days ♪

00:00:56.097 --> 00:00:59.517 position:50% align:center
♪ Worrying about what
the others think of me ♪

00:00:59.601 --> 00:01:03.229 position:50% align:center
♪ Sweet anxiety! ♪

00:01:03.313 --> 00:01:06.691 position:50% align:center
♪ This act is draining.
Oh, well, here it comes ♪

00:01:06.775 --> 00:01:14.908 position:50% align:center
♪ I'd better play dumber.
This long hot summer ♪

00:01:21.539 --> 00:01:26.628 position:50% align:center
[BOTH] ♪ But honestly,
I wish someone would say ♪

00:01:26.711 --> 00:01:28.463 position:50% align:center
[UTANO]
♪ "It's perfectly acceptable ♪

00:01:28.546 --> 00:01:30.340 position:50% align:center
♪ to spend all summer long ♪

00:01:30.423 --> 00:01:32.300 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU] ♪ At home alone
in total darkness ♪

00:01:32.384 --> 00:01:34.678 position:50% align:center
♪ with the A. C. on high" ♪

00:01:34.761 --> 00:01:39.641 position:50% align:center
[BOTH] ♪ Go ahead and skip
those music festivals, yeah! ♪

00:01:39.724 --> 00:01:42.644 position:50% align:center
♪ Uh-oh, the mosquito
escaped me again ♪

00:01:42.727 --> 00:01:46.856 position:50% align:center
♪ and now I can't
get to sleep. ♪

00:01:46.940 --> 00:01:50.276 position:50% align:center
♪ When I came back home,
to my abysmal dismay, ♪

00:01:50.360 --> 00:01:53.988 position:50% align:center
♪ the A. C. remote was gone ♪

00:01:54.072 --> 00:01:57.534 position:50% align:center
♪ My shirt's really gross
and covered in sweat. ♪

00:01:57.617 --> 00:02:01.413 position:50% align:center
♪ We've only just begun,
and it's such a huge bummer. ♪

00:02:01.496 --> 00:02:07.919 position:50% align:center
♪ This long hot summer! ♪

00:02:14.342 --> 00:02:15.844 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA grunts]

00:02:17.887 --> 00:02:20.181 position:50% align:center
It was so cold that day.

00:02:20.265 --> 00:02:22.475 position:50% align:center
[UTANO]
And now it's ridiculously hot.

00:02:22.559 --> 00:02:24.352 position:50% align:center
I'm actually kinda missing it.

00:02:24.436 --> 00:02:27.188 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI] Been a way
hotter year than usual.

00:02:27.272 --> 00:02:28.940 position:50% align:center
Ahh...

00:02:29.024 --> 00:02:30.900 position:50% align:center
True that, but it's
a whole lot worse

00:02:30.984 --> 00:02:33.319 position:50% align:center
riding it out in a mascot suit.

00:02:33.403 --> 00:02:36.072 position:50% align:center
Yeah, but we shoot in an
air-conditioned space,

00:02:36.156 --> 00:02:36.948 position:50% align:center
so there's that.

00:02:37.032 --> 00:02:38.783 position:50% align:center
[OTHERS chuckle]

00:02:38.867 --> 00:02:40.118 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
Yep.

00:02:40.201 --> 00:02:41.953 position:50% align:center
Yo, team!

00:02:42.037 --> 00:02:45.290 position:50% align:center
I hope you're all feeling
outdoorsy today!

00:02:47.584 --> 00:02:49.627 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA]
We're gonna be outside all day

00:02:49.711 --> 00:02:52.380 position:50% align:center
shooting this year's
winter music video!

00:02:52.464 --> 00:02:55.592 position:50% align:center
It's called "Subzero Spiral"!

00:02:55.675 --> 00:02:57.552 position:50% align:center
Go ahead and get changed
into your winter clothes,

00:02:57.635 --> 00:02:59.387 position:50% align:center
if you would!

00:02:59.471 --> 00:03:02.599 position:50% align:center
<i>Ganbaroh</i> , buds!

00:04:53.668 --> 00:04:55.628 position:50% align:center
Right. Now, let's do this!

00:04:55.712 --> 00:04:58.923 position:50% align:center
It's gonna be a music
video masterpiece!

00:05:01.092 --> 00:05:03.428 position:50% align:center
[ALL groan]

00:05:03.511 --> 00:05:05.013 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI] If we're
shooting winter scenes,

00:05:05.096 --> 00:05:07.223 position:50% align:center
couldn't we just tape
in-studio like normal?

00:05:07.307 --> 00:05:08.600 position:50% align:center
Are you kidding me?

00:05:08.683 --> 00:05:11.561 position:50% align:center
If it takes place in winter,
it needs to be snowing!

00:05:11.644 --> 00:05:13.855 position:50% align:center
Well, obviously, the snow itself

00:05:13.938 --> 00:05:16.358 position:50% align:center
will have to be added in post
because it's summer,

00:05:16.441 --> 00:05:19.069 position:50% align:center
but it's about feel, right?

00:05:19.152 --> 00:05:21.946 position:50% align:center
We have the feel,
and we need to keep it.

00:05:22.030 --> 00:05:24.657 position:50% align:center
CG backgrounds are so sterile!

00:05:24.741 --> 00:05:26.868 position:50% align:center
Oh! And as far as the feel goes,

00:05:26.951 --> 00:05:30.205 position:50% align:center
we also brought a space
heater and a <i>kotatsu</i> !

00:05:31.748 --> 00:05:33.875 position:50% align:center
Cool. So, first off,
try the song

00:05:33.958 --> 00:05:36.211 position:50% align:center
and see how the
video flows, 'kay?

00:05:36.294 --> 00:05:39.798 position:50% align:center
Make sure to sound wintery.
Countin' on you, bud!

00:05:39.881 --> 00:05:41.841 position:50% align:center
Oh, sure.

00:05:41.925 --> 00:05:45.053 position:50% align:center
But don't they dub the
audio in at the end?

00:05:50.684 --> 00:05:53.019 position:50% align:center
♪ To trod in snow is
a dangerous path. ♪

00:05:53.103 --> 00:05:54.396 position:50% align:center
♪ Be careful,
it's a hazard. ♪

00:05:54.479 --> 00:05:58.441 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA] Not even close!
Not hearing the winter!

00:05:59.526 --> 00:06:01.319 position:50% align:center
[BOTH groan]

00:06:04.447 --> 00:06:06.825 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU] ♪ To trod in snow
is a dangerous path. ♪

00:06:06.908 --> 00:06:09.119 position:50% align:center
♪ Be careful,
it's a hazard. ♪

00:06:09.202 --> 00:06:11.079 position:50% align:center
♪ If you take off too fast, ♪

00:06:11.162 --> 00:06:12.997 position:50% align:center
♪ you'll fall down
just like that. ♪

00:06:13.081 --> 00:06:15.208 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA]
Stop! Stop!

00:06:15.291 --> 00:06:18.253 position:50% align:center
You're not giving me
any trace of frostiness!

00:06:18.336 --> 00:06:21.548 position:50% align:center
Iketeru, I need to hear
the winter in your voice,

00:06:21.631 --> 00:06:23.633 position:50% align:center
so give it to me already!

00:06:23.717 --> 00:06:27.303 position:50% align:center
Yes, sir. I'm really sorry.

00:06:27.387 --> 00:06:30.056 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
Winter. It's winter.

00:06:30.140 --> 00:06:33.226 position:50% align:center
I am in the middle of winter.

00:06:33.309 --> 00:06:36.271 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU] It's winter.
It's winter. It's winter.

00:06:36.354 --> 00:06:40.316 position:50% align:center
It's winter. It's winter.
It's winter...

00:06:40.400 --> 00:06:42.819 position:50% align:center
Iketeru Oniisan,
pull it back some!

00:06:42.902 --> 00:06:45.822 position:50% align:center
In this heat, your
talent could kill you!

00:06:45.905 --> 00:06:48.742 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
Wasn't working, either way.

00:06:48.825 --> 00:06:50.994 position:50% align:center
[UTANO]
Obviously.

00:06:51.077 --> 00:06:54.080 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU, UTANO]
<i>Uramichi Oniisan.</i>

00:06:54.164 --> 00:06:55.457 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA]
Good stuff, Iketeru!

00:06:55.540 --> 00:06:58.626 position:50% align:center
It's actually starting
to look like winter now!

00:06:58.710 --> 00:07:01.338 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] Hey, Uramichi.
What's that thing?

00:07:01.421 --> 00:07:03.631 position:50% align:center
Huh? What?

00:07:03.715 --> 00:07:05.258 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] That thing you're
holding with the face.

00:07:05.342 --> 00:07:08.720 position:50% align:center
Is it a snow...
uh, snow... snow m...

00:07:08.803 --> 00:07:10.930 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
It's obviously a snowman.

00:07:11.014 --> 00:07:12.807 position:50% align:center
They handed it to me
right when I showed up

00:07:12.891 --> 00:07:14.893 position:50% align:center
and told me to draw
a face on it.

00:07:14.976 --> 00:07:16.728 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Right.

00:07:16.811 --> 00:07:18.188 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
What about you?

00:07:18.271 --> 00:07:20.607 position:50% align:center
You're clutching that banana
like it's your only child.

00:07:20.690 --> 00:07:23.777 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] Oh! Heh.
Ennoshita gave it to me.

00:07:23.860 --> 00:07:25.945 position:50% align:center
She's all, "Could you
please eat this?"

00:07:26.029 --> 00:07:28.156 position:50% align:center
and I couldn't say no, y'know?

00:07:28.239 --> 00:07:31.117 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Right. You gonna eat it, then?

00:07:31.201 --> 00:07:33.161 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Sure, but I'm gonna cherish it

00:07:33.244 --> 00:07:34.621 position:50% align:center
as long as I can, first.

00:07:34.704 --> 00:07:35.955 position:50% align:center
It'll bruise.

00:07:36.039 --> 00:07:36.706 position:50% align:center
[KAYO]
Usao?

00:07:36.790 --> 00:07:39.709 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Uh! Y-Yes?

00:07:39.793 --> 00:07:42.629 position:50% align:center
You ready? Did you
finish the banana?

00:07:42.712 --> 00:07:44.673 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Oh, I figured I'd hold onto it

00:07:44.756 --> 00:07:46.800 position:50% align:center
until I had time
to really savor it.

00:07:46.883 --> 00:07:49.219 position:50% align:center
Right. Guess that's fair.

00:07:49.302 --> 00:07:52.514 position:50% align:center
And remember to keep the peel
once you finish it, 'kay?

00:07:52.597 --> 00:07:54.057 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Hm?

00:07:54.140 --> 00:07:56.351 position:50% align:center
[KAYO] Usao slips and falls on
the snow in the music video,

00:07:56.434 --> 00:07:58.311 position:50% align:center
but the thing is,
we don't have anything here

00:07:58.395 --> 00:08:02.273 position:50% align:center
for you to actually slip on,
hence, the banana peel.

00:08:02.357 --> 00:08:06.653 position:50% align:center
So, yeah, please hang onto
that peel once you're done.

00:08:06.736 --> 00:08:10.699 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Sure. Got it.

00:08:10.782 --> 00:08:13.993 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
A banana peel? Seriously?

00:08:14.911 --> 00:08:17.539 position:50% align:center
Guys, let's get it
in gear, okay?

00:08:17.622 --> 00:08:20.792 position:50% align:center
I'm not trying to kill
you, and here's proof!

00:08:20.875 --> 00:08:22.419 position:50% align:center
This <i>kotatsu</i> and heater?

00:08:22.502 --> 00:08:25.547 position:50% align:center
The trick is, they're not
actually plugged in!

00:08:25.630 --> 00:08:27.090 position:50% align:center
How's that a trick?

00:08:27.173 --> 00:08:28.008 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA]
What?

00:08:28.091 --> 00:08:29.426 position:50% align:center
What?

00:08:31.094 --> 00:08:33.054 position:50% align:center
[ALL groan]

00:08:33.138 --> 00:08:35.140 position:50% align:center
Okay, so the lyrics
on this part,

00:08:35.223 --> 00:08:38.768 position:50% align:center
"The air in the room froze white
like a cloudy midwinter sky."

00:08:38.852 --> 00:08:41.354 position:50% align:center
This is some next-level
coldness we got,

00:08:41.438 --> 00:08:42.814 position:50% align:center
so show me that.

00:08:42.897 --> 00:08:45.358 position:50% align:center
Give me a sense of
that extreme cold!

00:08:45.442 --> 00:08:47.318 position:50% align:center
It's like-- How do I put it?

00:08:47.402 --> 00:08:50.864 position:50% align:center
Colder than the coldest place
you've ever been. It's...

00:08:50.947 --> 00:08:54.242 position:50% align:center
So, is this <i>kotatsu</i>
really turned off?

00:08:54.325 --> 00:08:56.244 position:50% align:center
It's steamy under there.

00:08:56.327 --> 00:08:58.747 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA] What I'm getting
at is, this room you're in,

00:08:58.830 --> 00:09:01.124 position:50% align:center
it's so, so cold
in there, you guys.

00:09:01.207 --> 00:09:04.377 position:50% align:center
It is a really cold
room. Got that?

00:09:04.461 --> 00:09:07.088 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Right...

00:09:17.807 --> 00:09:21.770 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA] Okay, guys,
we're in the dead of winter.

00:09:21.853 --> 00:09:24.981 position:50% align:center
And it's super,
super cold, got it?

00:09:25.065 --> 00:09:27.359 position:50% align:center
Look! I think there's a
little flurry comin' in!

00:09:27.442 --> 00:09:28.902 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Huh?

00:09:28.985 --> 00:09:31.738 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
No, there definitely isn't.

00:09:31.821 --> 00:09:33.490 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA]
Look with your mind's eye!

00:09:33.573 --> 00:09:36.659 position:50% align:center
Uramichi! What's a good
drink on days like this?

00:09:36.743 --> 00:09:38.703 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
A nice frosty can of beer.

00:09:38.787 --> 00:09:41.873 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA] The air is frosty!
You want a warm <i>shiruko</i> !

00:09:41.956 --> 00:09:43.458 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Even imagining that is giving me

00:09:43.541 --> 00:09:45.502 position:50% align:center
the worst cottonmouth
I've ever had.

00:09:45.585 --> 00:09:47.879 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA]
Cripes. Utano! Same question!

00:09:47.962 --> 00:09:50.048 position:50% align:center
Beer. Any kind of beer on tap.

00:09:50.131 --> 00:09:52.759 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA]
No! Well, Iketeru?

00:09:52.842 --> 00:09:54.469 position:50% align:center
Ice cream soda.

00:09:54.552 --> 00:09:55.679 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI, UTANO]
That's cute.

00:09:55.762 --> 00:09:58.306 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA] Yeah, cute,
but it's also wrong!

00:09:58.390 --> 00:10:02.060 position:50% align:center
Fine then, we'll move on!
Time for the bonfire!

00:10:02.143 --> 00:10:04.729 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
You good, bro? Hey!

00:10:07.232 --> 00:10:09.192 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA grunts]

00:10:09.275 --> 00:10:11.903 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Uhh... Bro?

00:10:16.616 --> 00:10:22.747 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] Wait! Kumatani,
you can't-- Ow. Ow. Ow.

00:10:22.831 --> 00:10:24.416 position:50% align:center
Dude, core strength!

00:10:24.499 --> 00:10:27.377 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA groans]

00:10:29.879 --> 00:10:31.006 position:50% align:center
Mister Derekida.

00:10:31.089 --> 00:10:33.008 position:50% align:center
Uh, yes?

00:10:33.091 --> 00:10:35.260 position:50% align:center
Forgive me, but it's
not clicking with me.

00:10:35.343 --> 00:10:37.971 position:50% align:center
How would Kumao
perform this song?

00:10:38.054 --> 00:10:40.223 position:50% align:center
It might be because
I'm a visual learner.

00:10:40.306 --> 00:10:41.683 position:50% align:center
It would probably help

00:10:41.766 --> 00:10:44.519 position:50% align:center
if you could physically show
me what you have in mind.

00:10:44.602 --> 00:10:46.688 position:50% align:center
Uhh...

00:10:46.771 --> 00:10:48.857 position:50% align:center
Uh. Kumatani?

00:10:48.940 --> 00:10:52.277 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA]
Hey! What are you--? Stop it!

00:10:52.360 --> 00:10:55.405 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Whoa. Kumatani.

00:10:55.488 --> 00:10:57.073 position:50% align:center
[yells]

00:10:57.157 --> 00:11:00.869 position:50% align:center
Hot! How can people even
wear these things?

00:11:00.952 --> 00:11:05.331 position:50% align:center
Oh, God! I can't get out of it!

00:11:05.415 --> 00:11:07.709 position:50% align:center
Grrr...

00:11:11.588 --> 00:11:12.714 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:11:12.797 --> 00:11:14.507 position:50% align:center
[KAYO]
The director just passed out!

00:11:14.591 --> 00:11:15.842 position:50% align:center
[EDEI]
We're taking a medical break!

00:11:15.925 --> 00:11:18.678 position:50% align:center
Everyone back to
the studio, pronto!

00:11:20.513 --> 00:11:22.515 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] You know how he
quit his last job, right?

00:11:22.599 --> 00:11:25.352 position:50% align:center
By punching his power-tripping
supervisor in the face.

00:11:25.435 --> 00:11:26.436 position:50% align:center
[UTANO]
Uh...

00:11:26.519 --> 00:11:27.854 position:50% align:center
And he was really
good at that job,

00:11:27.937 --> 00:11:30.523 position:50% align:center
I mean, like fast-tracked
for a promotion.

00:11:30.607 --> 00:11:32.192 position:50% align:center
And he still did that?

00:11:32.275 --> 00:11:33.568 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah. Twice.

00:11:33.651 --> 00:11:37.614 position:50% align:center
Seriously? Does he
not learn? Or does he?

00:11:37.697 --> 00:11:40.742 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA]
<i>Uramichi Oniisan</i> ...

00:11:44.537 --> 00:11:46.331 position:50% align:center
Boy, I love air conditioning.

00:11:46.414 --> 00:11:49.084 position:50% align:center
I never knew how much
until yesterday's shoot.

00:11:49.167 --> 00:11:51.211 position:50% align:center
I guess maybe it's like
how takin' a long trip

00:11:51.294 --> 00:11:54.756 position:50% align:center
makes you realize how nice
things are back at home.

00:11:56.049 --> 00:11:57.717 position:50% align:center
What? How do you mean?

00:11:57.801 --> 00:11:59.094 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Oh, I dunno.

00:11:59.177 --> 00:12:01.638 position:50% align:center
Honestly, it felt kinda off
as soon as I said it.

00:12:01.721 --> 00:12:03.765 position:50% align:center
No, go ahead! I wanna know.

00:12:03.848 --> 00:12:05.100 position:50% align:center
Please! Just explain
what you said about...

00:12:05.183 --> 00:12:07.018 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] Seriously,
there's nothing to explain.

00:12:07.102 --> 00:12:08.978 position:50% align:center
What is this conversation?

00:12:09.062 --> 00:12:10.397 position:50% align:center
For real, though.

00:12:10.480 --> 00:12:12.357 position:50% align:center
I don't know how much worse
yesterday could've been.

00:12:12.440 --> 00:12:14.693 position:50% align:center
All that sunblock
didn't do anything.

00:12:14.776 --> 00:12:16.194 position:50% align:center
The only thing that saved us

00:12:16.277 --> 00:12:19.197 position:50% align:center
was Kumatani going off on
the director right at the end.

00:12:19.280 --> 00:12:22.158 position:50% align:center
We could've had casualties
if we kept going.

00:12:24.035 --> 00:12:26.204 position:50% align:center
Doin' a great job, team!

